Open Origin is based upon an economic model of circular systems found throughout nature. Using modern technologies to repurpose what is currently considered waste, utilizing a vertically integrated manufacturing model with interconnected processes, and designing for net-zero emissions yields returns far in excess of industry norms.  

While a typical green development project might have a DSCR of 1.5 to 2 and provide full ROI within 7 to 10 years, our projects run DSCRs as high as 7 and can provide full ROI in 2-3 years.  In addition, by partnering with and deploying our facilities on sovereign indigenous land, we can shave years off of a typical industrial development project, avoiding the red tape, while exceeding the environment standards of the surrounding regulatory domains.  By investing the latest technologies and industrial facilities into some of the most remote and previously under represented communities, Open Origin provides training, jobs, economic opportunity and sustainable growth where it was never before possible.

Join us. Let's build a better future for everyone, together, today.

Electro Scan Inc. is a leading supplier of Inspection, Testing, and Certification (ITC) products and services for the pipe condition assessment & pipe certification market. The Company represents a disruptive technology that is overhauling how new and rehabilitated pipelines are inspected and certified as watertight, including trenchless rehabilitation, Cured-in-Place Pipe (CIPP), and Spray-In-Place Pipe (SIPP) products. A key advantage is ability to automatically identify & measure defects in Gallons Per Minute (GPM) or Liters Per Second (LPS) not found by Acoustic, Closed-Circuit Television (CCTV), Electro-Magnetic, Laser, LiDAR, Pressure Gradient, Sonar, and other legacy inspection methods.

Electro Scan Inc., a GovTech 100 company, provides financial stewardship for water utilities and smart cities by maximizing the useful life of their sewer & water pipes and independent environmental governance certifying the watertight condition of contractor delivered repairs, rehabilitation, and replacement pipelines, including trenchless pipe materials.
